title: Malibu
name: Reel Inn
content: Malibu's upscale version of fast food, the ordering process at Reel Inn is simple: choose a fish, two sides, and either salad or cole slaw, as well as both alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks, and then wait at a bench (indoors and outdoors) while your food is prepared.  The fish is good, the prices are reasonable, and the atmosphere is friendly.  Valet parking is mandatory on weekends, and parking attendants have been known to mix up keys.
